HEADWORD: Cenogamy
<hw>Ce*nog"a*my</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*n⟦ocr⟧g"⟦adot⟧*m⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>koino`s</grk> common + <grk>ga`mos</grk>
marriage.]</ety> <def>The state of a community which permits promiscuous
sexual intercourse among its members, as in certain societies practicing
communism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>cenogenesis</ent>⟦br⟧
